Title: The UV and IR Origin of Nonabelian Chiral Gauge Anomalies on

Noncommutative Minkowski Space-timeAuthors: C.P. Martin (Universidad Complutense de Madrid)

Comments: PlainTex, 21 pages, 2 eps figures, corrected some typos

Journal-ref: J.Phys. A34 (2001) 9037-9056

We discuss both the UV and IR origin of the one-loop triangle gauge anomaliesfor noncommutative nonabelian chiral gauge theories with fundamental, adjointand bi-fundamental fermions for U(N) groups. We find that gauge anomalies onlycome from planar triangle diagrams, the non-planar triangle contributionsgiving rise to no breaking of the Ward identies. Generally speaking, theorieswith fundamental and bi-fundamental chiral matter are anomalous. Theories withonly adjoint chiral fermions are anomaly free.